	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Apr 16th 12:10 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=16337><span id= >vhoghul</span></a><br><span id=notbold>26 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>We're not necessarily talking about just using this shield. But Shield of Rainbow Hues, Net of the Deep Sea and the Orb of the Infinite Void are widely used by monks for pulling mobs.<br><br>When you are going out alone to pull a mob that can kill you in 25 seconds of beatings, hoping to seperate him from his 2 friends that can shorten that time down to 5 seconds, you need all the help you can get in case feign fails, and a shield is alot of help. The plan would be to hit your stone stance button, face the mobs and hope your hp and resists save you long enough to attempt a feign again. The shields add to your AC, hp and Resists, making it very worthwhile to equip a shield when pulling dangerous mobs.<br><br>And anyone who has played a bard can attst to how easy it eventually becomes to swap out slots for other more needed items. It jus tbecomes second nature eventually with the right Hot Buttons.<br><br>Now this shield in particular is a little heavy to be of much use to a monk, so I can't imagine many benefits to a monk for having it. But there are uses for shield for monks too.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
